> Edit: I should also mention that SSTU is really intended to be played with most stock (and other mods') parts removed or disabled
> 

Janitor's Closet is my best friend for removing 99% of stock parts ![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif ":)")   It renames the cfg/mu files so they will not even load the next time you start KSP.

The <abbr title="Module Manager (mod)">MM</abbr> patch to scale engines:

    @PART[partname]:NEEDS[SSTU]:AFTER[SSTU]
    {
        @MODULE[SSTUModularEngineCluster]
        {
            @engineScale = 1.0
        }
    }

